description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridge University Hospitals (CUH) NHS Foundation Trust comprises Addenbrooke’s Hospital and the Rosie Hospital in Cambridge. With over 11000 staff and over 1100 beds the priorities of the Trust focus on a quality service which is all about people – patients, staff and partners. Recognised as providing ‘outstanding’ care to our patients and rated ‘Good’ overall by the Care Quality Commissioner, is testament to the skill and dedication of the people who work here. CUH’s values – Together- safe, kind, excellent – are at the heart of patient care, defining the way all staff work and behave. The Trust provides accessible high-quality healthcare for the local people of Cambridge, together with specialist services, dealing with rare or complex conditions for a regional, national and international population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting and challenging opportunity has arisen for a Band 4 Administrator to provide an efficient and effective administrative service for the NHS England Highly Specialised Service for Type Two Neurofibromatosis (NF2). This service works on a hub/spoke model with the post based in Cambridge but providing support to the spoke services in Birmingham, Leicester and Nottingham (Eastern/Midland region) for all its users including patients, relatives and colleagues.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, committed individual with a good knowledge of database management and good communication skills. You will need to be flexible and organised in your approach and have the ability to prioritise workloads efficiently. Evidence of working effectively as an individual and as a member of a Multidisciplinary team is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be involved in providing coordination &amp; support to the NF2 Team to include assistance in the preparation of the MDT, the provision of telephone triage to people contacting the service, PA support to the specialist nursing team and other administrative support work tasks for professionals within the team. You will be responsible for the collection and submission of data including scan results and other data for clinical audit for the local and national clinical team to review.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be given the opportunity to work with a Multi-disciplinary team who are committed to continuing to provide excellent care to people with NF2 and receive a tremendous amount of satisfaction in having a varied role within an exciting service.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits to you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer development opportunities and a wide range of benefits including on-site leisure facilities, shopping concourse, day nurseries and access to a great transport system with easy access to airports and rail travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details of our fantastic benefits please refer to the attachment below - CUH Benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note if you would like to discuss the required hours of this role further, you should approach the contact given. In some cases alternative working hours will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from the Armed Forces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Nicola Gamazo, Email address: Nicola.gamazo@addenbrookes.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Juliette Buttimore, at Juliette.buttimore@addenbrookes.nhs.uk or on tel. 01223 348672&lt;/p&gt;
